HEADWORD: Priscillianist
<hw>Pris*cil"lian*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A follower of <ets>Priscillian</ets>, bishop of Avila
in Spain, in the fourth century, who mixed various elements of
Gnosticism and Manicheism with Christianity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

